name: Mijyi

reviews.text: Nice selection of goods at this shop, had an interesting time looking around. Nice alternative to Daiso.

I’m very upset of the staff I never come across so bad service in this Kallang. The staff face is like so angry you ask anything you are very unhappy. I really cannot expect the is so bad service I really cannot expect have the shop. The staff  is so unhappy and not really welcome people come inside and buy something I hope the company manage please do something about your staff If you are not welcome people to buy something please close the shop and don’t show the angry face like not happy very very upset for the staff

I came here to browse but did not buy anything as the items are a little old, random and do not seem to be of great quality. The place is similar to Daiso, although the items are more expensive and probably not even as good quality and not as much choice as Daiso.

Most items at this store are very old and in bad condition. It's a waste of a massive retail prime space. Has close to none visitors given the items are not even priced cheap. Competitors such as daisoband shoppee are selling far cheaper and better quality products. Owner should consider letting go of old inventory online (such as at shoppee / lazada) in bulk deal discounts and consider taking a franchise such as miniso, daiso .. etc
Bought a cable here only for me to bring it home and realise it is not working at all. It is indeed cheap but buying unusable stuffs isn’t really worth it.
